  "notes": "Moksha (мокшень кяль), Mordvinic (Uralic), Russia. Written in a Cyrillic alphabet identical in inventory to Russian. Palatalisation is phonemic and is written the Russian way (soft sign <ь>, iotated vowel letters <е ё ю я>), which is why those letters map to a palatalising sequence. Moksha additionally has voiceless sonorants, spelled <лх>, <рх>, <йх>. The reduced vowel /ə/ is not given its own letter — it is spelled <о>/<е>/<а> depending on context — so it appears here only as an allophone. Stress is largely on the first syllable but is not written.",
